  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We propose two different and complementary observables for singling out possible signals of physics beyond the Standard Model (SM) in the semi-leptonic decays Λb → Λcℓν̄ℓ, both with the τ lepton and with a light lepton. The two observables are the partial decay width and a T-odd asymmetry, whose respective sensitivities to scalar and/or pseudo-scalar coupling are calculated as functions of the parameters characterizing new physics (NP). Two different form factors are used. Three particular cases are discussed and analyzed in detail.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">World Scientific</subfield>
